Reveille is in essence a wake-up call to revive the opulence that is dormant in all of us. A sense of renewal, while we rework the classics that define fashion. The word reveille is a French word that means, to wake up. Ritika Mirchandani’s newest collection, emotes this very spirit or revival, while its designs are inspired by the grandeur and opulence of the Art Deco era of the ‘20s. Featuring the brand’s signature bugle beading work and silhouettes like sharara sets and pre-pleated saris, the collection also reinvents the staples and introduces new designs.

latestPosts.caption:
"DELICATELY BOLD"✨

@krithi.shetty_official in #RitikaMirchandani 

FROM THE FIRST STITCH TO THE FINAL SILHOUETTE, THIS LOOK IS BUILT ON TEXTURE, DEPTH, AND DETAIL.

EACH ELEMENT OF THE EMBROIDERY IS METICULOUSLY HANDCRAFTED USING BUGLE BEADS, DORI, AND METAL SEQUINS WITH ARTISANAL PRECISION. THE EMBELLISHMENTS ARE RICHLY TEXTURED YET DELIBERATELY RESTRAINED, DESIGNED TO CATCH THE LIGHT WITHOUT COMPETING WITH THE SILHOUETTE.

THE LOOK IS A SEAMLESS BALANCE OF STRUCTURE AND SENSUALITY A BOLD REINTERPRETATION OF POWER DRESSING, SEEN THROUGH THE LENS OF COUTURE CRAFTSMANSHIP.
